what information is kept in the audit trail and how will it be used stanford answers stanford university stanford answers what information is kept in the audit trail and how will it be used categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home what information is kept in the audit trail and how will it be used search this site computers that use the stanford whole disk encryption swde solution are set up to check in with a logging and administrative server on a regular basis in the event of loss or theft there will be an audit trail of the encryption status of the computer the purpose of the audit trail is to document the known state of the computer at the time the computer was lost or went missing audit trail information includes but is not limited to the state of the computer encrypted encrypting decrypted whether a passphrase was required after 15 30 minutes of inactivity and whether the required registry settings were correctly set as of the last time checked the audit trail helps stanford determine whether the data is secure or if the people whose data was lost or stolen should be notified workstation encryption workstation encryption stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
